000-0003-3819-8537",{"_":201,"xml:id":202,"ref":203},"James Cummings","JCu","http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6686-3728",{"_":205,"xml:id":206,"ref":207},"Simona Stoyanova","SS","https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3914-9569",{"_":209,"when":210,"who":194},"updated bibliography plus named entities","2022-02-17",{"n":99,"url":100,"height":101,"width":102,"desc":103,"surfaceType":104},[],[214,215,216,217,218,219],"Kaibel, 1890, IG","Castelli, 1769, Siciliae et objacentium insularum veterum inscriptionum nova collectio","Castelli, 1784, Siciliae et objacentium insularum veterum inscriptionum nova collectio prolegomenis et notis illustrata, et iterum cum emendationibus, & auctariis evulgata","Boeckh, Franz, 1853, CIG","Russo, 1911, Illustrazione storico-archeologica di Adernò","Prag, 2015, Epigrafia",[221,222,223,224,225,226],"Q2SBPG9F","SPTB56H3","7PSFHSUH","TQMVHEVL","CRSSWMDV","SHKXSQLC",[228,229,230,23,29,33,231,232,233,234,29,235,108],"isic001387","fragmentary greek inscription (funerary?)",{"_":5},"adranon","adrano","sicilia","sicily","ancient greek",[],{"title":238,"body":239,"divs":240,"editions":265,"images":275,"handnote":281},"ISic001387. Fragmentary Greek inscription (funerary?)","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ἀρχε\n                    ας\n                    Πολυσ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἀρχε\n                    ας\">Ἀρχε[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ας\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Πολυσ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Πολυσ\">Πολυσ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ἀρχε\n                    ας\n                    Πολυσ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἀρχε\n                    ας\">ΑΡΧΕ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΑΣ\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Πολυσ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Πολυσ\">ΠΟΛΥΣ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001387_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001387_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001387.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001387-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text derived from Torremuzza 1769\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 3\">line.3: \u003Cspan>Torremuzza gives no indication that anything is missing after the sigma\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The stone is probably a funerary inscription. Franz (\u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/TQMVHEVL\" target=\"_blank\">CIG\u003C/a> III, 5737) proposed expanding the text as Ἀρχε[λαΐδ]ας Πολυσ[τράτου] or Πολυσ[θένευς] (i.e. “(tombstone) of Archelaidas, son of Polystratos/Polysthenes”). However, the name \u003Ca href=\"http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?name=%E1%BC%88%CF%81%CF%87%CE%B5%CE%BB%CE%B1%CE%90%CE%B4%CE%B1%CF%82\" target=\"_blank\">Ἀρχελαΐδας\u003C/a> is not attested for Sicily, and the alternatives in Ἀρχε- known for the island mostly do not end in –ας (Ἀρχέδαμος is common; Ἀρχεθάλης, Ἀρχέλας, Ἀρχέστρατος, Ἀρχέτιμος, Ἀρχέτιος are all found). \u003Ca href=\"http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?name=%CE%A0%CE%BF%CE%BB%CF%8D%CF%83%CF%84%CF%81%CE%B1%CF%84%CE%BF%CF%82\" target=\"_blank\">Πολύστρατος\u003C/a> is attested once on Sicily, \u003Ca href=\"http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?name=%CE%A0%CE%BF%CE%BB%CF%85%CF%83%CE%B8%CE%AD%CE%BD%CE%B7%CF%82\" target=\"_blank\">Πολυσθένης\u003C/a> is rare and not known in western Greece/Sicily. Torremuzza does not indicate anything was missing after the final letter, and the rare name \u003Ca href=\"http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?name=%CE%A0%CF%8C%CE%BB%CF%85%CF%82\" target=\"_blank\">Πόλυς\u003C/a> is attested in Sicily, on a vase inscription from Gela of the fifth century BC (Dubois, IGDS 142 c; = Arena, Iscr. Sic. II 23), although one would then expect Πολυος for the genitive patronymic.\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>It is impossible to date this text, in the absence of further information, although it is most likely to belong to the Hellenistic period.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Castelli 1769 \u003Ca href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buchseite/501560\" target=\"_blank\">268 cl. 18 no. 38\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1784 \u003Ca href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buchseite/501990\" target=\"_blank\">287 cl. 18 no. 38\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Franz 1853 5737 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">568\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Russo 1911 59-60 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001615\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001615\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Prag 2015 317-318 no. B \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002338\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002338\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Since the text is only recorded in the second-hand transcription by Torremuzza, nothing reliable can be said about the letter-forms.\u003C/p> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  \u003C/div>",[241,244,247,250,253,256,259,262],{"id":242,"html":243},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ἀρχε\n                    ας\n                    Πολυσ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἀρχε\n                    ας\">Ἀρχε[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ας\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Πολυσ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Πολυσ\">Πολυσ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ἀρχε\n                    ας\n                    Πολυσ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἀρχε\n                    ας\">ΑΡΧΕ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΑΣ\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Πολυσ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Πολυσ\">ΠΟΛΥΣ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":245,"html":246},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001387_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001387_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001387.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001387-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":248,"html":249},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text derived from Torremuzza 1769\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 3\">line.3: \u003Cspan>Torremuzza gives no indication that anything is missing after the sigma\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":251,"html":252},"translation","\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>",{"id":254,"html":255},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The stone is probably a funerary inscription. Franz (\u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/TQMVHEVL\" target=\"_blank\">CIG\u003C/a> III, 5737) proposed expanding the text as Ἀρχε[λαΐδ]ας Πολυσ[τράτου] or Πολυσ[θένευς] (i.e. “(tombstone) of Archelaidas, son of Polystratos/Polysthenes”). However, the name \u003Ca href=\"http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?name=%E1%BC%88%CF%81%CF%87%CE%B5%CE%BB%CE%B1%CE%90%CE%B4%CE%B1%CF%82\" target=\"_blank\">Ἀρχελαΐδας\u003C/a> is not attested for Sicily, and the alternatives in Ἀρχε- known for the island mostly do not end in –ας (Ἀρχέδαμος is common; Ἀρχεθάλης, Ἀρχέλας, Ἀρχέστρατος, Ἀρχέτιμος, Ἀρχέτιος are all found). \u003Ca href=\"http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?name=%CE%A0%CE%BF%CE%BB%CF%8D%CF%83%CF%84%CF%81%CE%B1%CF%84%CE%BF%CF%82\" target=\"_blank\">Πολύστρατος\u003C/a> is attested once on Sicily, \u003Ca href=\"http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?name=%CE%A0%CE%BF%CE%BB%CF%85%CF%83%CE%B8%CE%AD%CE%BD%CE%B7%CF%82\" target=\"_blank\">Πολυσθένης\u003C/a> is rare and not known in western Greece/Sicily. Torremuzza does not indicate anything was missing after the final letter, and the rare name \u003Ca href=\"http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?name=%CE%A0%CF%8C%CE%BB%CF%85%CF%82\" target=\"_blank\">Πόλυς\u003C/a> is attested in Sicily, on a vase inscription from Gela of the fifth century BC (Dubois, IGDS 142 c; = Arena, Iscr. Sic. II 23), although one would then expect Πολυος for the genitive patronymic.\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>It is impossible to date this text, in the absence of further information, although it is most likely to belong to the Hellenistic period.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":257,"html":258},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Castelli 1769 \u003Ca href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buchseite/501560\" target=\"_blank\">268 cl. 18 no. 38\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1784 \u003Ca href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buchseite/501990\" target=\"_blank\">287 cl. 18 no. 38\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Franz 1853 5737 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">568\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Russo 1911 59-60 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001615\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001615\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Prag 2015 317-318 no. B \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002338\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002338\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":260,"html":261},"handnote","\u003Cp>Since the text is only recorded in the second-hand transcription by Torremuzza, nothing reliable can be said about the letter-forms.\u003C/p> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":263,"html":264},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  ",[266,268,271,272],{"html":267},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag",{"id":269,"lang":108,"html":270},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ἀρχε\n                    ας\n                    Πολυσ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἀρχε\n                    ας\">Ἀρχε[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003